comments: Looney (GSW) and Sabonis (SAC) mutually engage and disengage in marginal contact off-ball.
Green (GSW) briefly grasps Barnes' (SAC) arm as Green positions himself to receive the ball in the post.
Barnes (SAC) places a collapsed forearm against Looney's (GSW) side and marginal contact occurs as Barnes releases while contesting the shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) slightly extends his arm into Looney's (GSW) back and marginal contact occurs as Sabonis defends the shot attempt at the rim.
Green's (GSW) hand slides off of Barnes' (SAC) off-arm as he is retreating backward while contesting Barnes' driving shot attempt.
Wiggins (GSW) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects Sabonis' (SAC) shot attempt.

Green (GSW) contest the shot attempt and makes contact with the ball, while following though, he makes incidental contact with Sabonis' (SAC) face during the rebounding opportunity.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Green (GSW) is set in Mitchell's (SAC) path and is firming up on his right leg as the pick is set.
Sabonis (SAC) is set in Curry's (GSW) path and both players engage in marginal contact as the pick is set.
Looney (GSW) makes incidental high-five contact with Fox (SAC) after the release of his shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Wiggins (GSW) makes incidental contact with Monk's (SAC) arm as both players pursue the rebound attempt.
Thompson (GSW) jumps alongside Monk's (SAC) path and maintains verticality as he absorbs the contact initiated by Monk during the driving shot attempt.
The Golden State Warriors had exceeded the number of timeouts allowed when Curry (GSW) requested a timeout.
Green (GSW) reaches across and makes contact with Fox's (SAC) arm, affecting his dribble.
Wiggins (GSW) avoids initiating contact with Barnes' (SAC) as he is contesting the jump shot.
Sabonis (SAC) briefly grasps Looney's (GSW) arm as both players position themselves for the rebound.
Thompson (GSW) is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession was correctly awarded to Sacramento.
Green (GSW) avoids initiating illegal contact with Fox (SAC) as he is contesting the shot attempt.
Curry (GSW) briefly rests his off-arm on Fox's (SAC) opposite hip during his drive toward the rim.
Sabonis (SAC) briefly grasps Looney's (GSW) arm as both players position themselves for the rebound.
Curry (GSW) avoids initiating contact with Barnes (SAC) as he is contesting the jump shot.
